  5. Test Design: Error Handling Patterns (106 test errors)

  What MyPy is teaching us:
  Many [union-attr] errors in test files show inconsistent error handling patterns in tests.

  Pattern seen in test_result_simplified.py (34 errors):
  # ❌ Tests directly accessing .error without type narrowing
  def test_basic_failure():
      result = Result.fail(Errors.system("error"))
      assert result.error.message == "error"  # [union-attr]

  # ✅ Use .expect_error() consistently
  def test_basic_failure():
      result = Result.fail(Errors.system("error"))
      error = result.expect_error()
      assert error.message == "error"

  Architectural lesson: "Test patterns should match production patterns"
  - Tests should demonstrate the correct usage patterns
  - Using .expect_error() in tests shows other developers how to use it

